synopsis : - - large - scale development of the west is a key strategy of our country 's cross - century macroeconomic development that is of vital significance .
- - large - scale development of the west is a magnificent project that requires overall planning and all - round consideration as well as long - term struggle , that must adhere to certain basic principles .
- - large - scale development of the west has a bearing on the overall situation ; great efforts should be made to support it in such things as policy , system , capital , and talent , together with comprehensive planning and step - by - step implementation .
the western part of our country is a vast territory with rich natural resources and huge development potential .
but since reform and opening up , the economic development of the west has been relatively slow , leading to a wider gap with the economy of the east .
the economic discrepancy and contradiction between the east and the west has become an outstanding issue of our country 's macroeconomic operation .
at present , with the enhancement of our country 's economic strength , speeding up the development of the west is not only of vital significance but the condition is also ripe .
speeding up the development of the west helps boost the economic strength of the west , narrow the gap between regional economies , and harmonize regional economic development .
over the past 10 years , owing to the government 's moderately preferential macroeconomic policy , the economy of the west has been growing at a markedly improved rate , with certain important indexes even higher than that in the east .
however , an undeniable fact is that the economic gap between the east and the west is getting wider and wider .
for example , from 1978 to 1997 , as far as the proportion to the nationwide gdp is concerned , the east was up from 52 percent to 61.4 percent , while the west was down from 17 percent to 14.8 percent .
the gap in per capita gdp is also getting wider and wider .
in the early days of reform and opening up , the per capita gdp of northwestern provinces and regions was higher than that of fujian , and the figure of qinghai was even higher than that of guangdong .
but in 1997 , the nationwide per capita gdp was 6,392 yuan , while the per capita gdp of the west was merely 4,009 yuan , which was about 62.7 percent of the national average .
in 1998 , the per capita gdp of guangdong and fujian exceeded 10,000 yuan , while for the five northwestern provinces and regions , only xinjiang reached 6,435 yuan , but the rest were less than 4,500 yuan , and the difference was over 100 percent .
since reform and opening up , proceeding from the actual conditions of our country , letting some of the regions get rich first has been an absolutely correct policy to pursue .
but our goal is to achieve common prosperity .
unexploited land throughout the territory is close to 800 million acres , so there is huge potential for development .
they also have very rich tourism resources .
speeding up development of the west can facilitate rational allocation and flow of all kinds of resources and provide much room and huge driving force for the development of the national economy .
hence , in order to display the superiority of the west , fully utilize natural resources , bring about rational division of labor between regions , and strengthen the development momentum of the national economy , speeding up development of the west is truly essential .
speeding up development of the west helps increase domestic demand .
by the end of 1999 , the factory price index of production means and the overall retail price level of social consumables have dropped for 27 consecutive months .
social demands , including demands for investment , consumption , and export , are the key factor that stimulates economic growth .
our country is a big nation , the contribution rate of domestic demand to economic growth is far higher than export demand .
in particular , under the current situation of extremely fierce competition in the international market , a growing number of factors of price uncertainty , and volatile market changes , taking the expansion of domestic demand as the mainstay is also an important measure to lower economic risks .
speeding up development of the west helps increase domestic demand .
speeding up development of the west helps raise the material and cultural living standard of residents in the west .
at present , there is a fairly large gap between the material and cultural living standard of urban and rural residents in the west and their counterparts in the east .
large - scale development of the west will certainly quicken the pace of economic growth in the west , increase local urban and rural residents ' job opportunities and earnings , and create conditions for improving residents ' material and cultural lives .
our country is a multi - national state , whereas the west is a territory inhabited by minority nationalities .
economic development is the material foundation of social stability , political unity , and strong ethnic cohesiveness .
the basic principles of development of the west large - scale development of the west is an undertaking of great strategic significance and a cross - century project that requires overall planning and all - round consideration , as well as long - term struggle .
smash the limitations of the theory of economic and technological evolution , dare to develop by leaps and bounds .
for a long time , the concept of evolution has been popular , holding that economic and technological development can only proceed from the east to the west step by step .
this is the mode of thinking shaped under the conditions of a planned economy .
under the conditions of a planned economy , regional economic development relies entirely on the state 's investment and policy support and can only evolve according to the state 's set plan .
however , under the conditions of a market economy , there is no need for any of the regions to " wait " and " rely on others , " they can totally depend on their own strength , and seize the opportunity to develop at a faster pace .
whoever can seize the opportunity to bring its superiority into play can develop faster than others , or even surpass economically developed areas and develop by leaps and bounds .
take reform as the axis of the overall situation , vigorously quicken the pace of reform .
some people hold that economically backward areas should also lag behind in reform .
this is not law .
so in order to speed up development , reform must be expedited .
in reforming the state - owned economy , we should uphold the practice of going ahead in certain areas while backing off from others , take concrete measures to gradually withdraw from spheres that can be withdrawn , and make an inventory of state - owned assets .
to speed up reform , we must , first of all , change the way people think , particularly changing the way leading cadres think .
reform will bring about some new problems and new contradictions , or even infringe on certain people 's interests .
but if there is no reform and no economic development , there will be even more problems and more intense contradictions , and not only the interests of certain people but also the interests of the overwhelming majority that will be infringed upon .
reform of course brings risks , but there will be greater risks if we do not reform or put off reform .
hence , as far as large - scale development of the west is concerned , we must reform with greater intensity and promote development with reform .
stick to the two opening - up drives , be simultaneously open to other parts of the country and to foreign countries .
in the new century , the process of economic globalization will keep accelerating .
with its rich natural and labor resources and vast market , the west is very attractive to foreign investors .
to speed up development of the west , the government has to implement policies of foreign investment that are even more preferential than in the east , so as to attract more foreign capital .
at the same time , we must also attach great importance to investment from the east .
we must not only give preferential policy treatment to foreign investors but also to investors from the east and from the central part of the country . we must not only give preferential policy treatment to the public economic sector but also to the non - public economic sector .
to develop the west , we must not only utilize foreign resources and markets , but also utilize the resources and markets of the east and of the central part of the country .
sticking to the two opening - up drives is a must for speeding up development of the west .
vigorously develop the non - public economic sector .
the non - public economic sector is an important component of the socialist market economy .
vigorously developing the non - public economic sector is a must for speeding up development of the west and is of vital significance .
enable market - oriented development of the economy of the west in accordance with the law of market economy .
now as far as large - scale development of the west is concerned , we should never repeat what " remote - area " construction did but should rely on the propelling force of the market .
however , we must also stress that development of the west is a key strategic plan and the government also plays a vital role in it .
as proven by the experience of the united states and some other countries , in the development process of backward areas , government support in such respects as planning , coordination , policy - making , and funding is very essential .
integrating the " invisible hand " with the " visible hand " helps quicken the pace of development of the west .
