some people even optimistically predicted that china and the eu would conclude an agreement at the beginning of this year and china 's wto entry was just around the corner .
nevertheless , the results of the new round of consultations between china and the eu , which was held in brussels in late - january , showed that things were not so simple as imagined .
a reporter of the weekly " jingji daobao , " which just published its latest issue , dispatched back a report telling where the crux of the problem lies .
according to the report , after making an detailed analysis of the contents of the agreement reached by china and the united states , the eu stated that there was still " 20 percent of special interests " calling for negotiations with china .
the report pointed out : there is no way for the eu and china to sign an agreement at one go , and the process of negotiations will be quite difficult .
